The `checkPrimes` function takes an array of 5 numbers as input and checks if any of the numbers are prime. It first checks if the input array has exactly 5 numbers, throwing an error if it doesn't.

The `isPrime` function checks if a single number is prime. It uses a simple algorithm to check divisibility up to the square root of the number.

